NOVA - Manage virtual machines running on a cluster

*** Document Convention ***

difference between "delete" and "remove"
  delete: destroy existing resource
  remove: remove an item from a collection

CORE
====

Models
------

Group
  special groups: root (developer), admin (administrators), applying (applying users)
    root is more powerful than admin
    admin could add groups
  * has_many users


User
  special user: root
  * has_many groups
  * has_many vclusters
  * has_many vmachines

Vmachine
  * belong_to a user
  * belong_to many guest_users [experimental]
  * belong_to a vcluster (or not)

Vcluster
  * has_many vmachines

Pmachine
  before adding a new pmachine, we should authenticate it
  * has_may vmachines


Controllers
-----------

Group
  add_group
  delete_group
  add_member
  remove_member
  list_members (root?)

User
  add_user
  delete_user
  list_users (root?)

Pmachine
  add_pmachine (authentication required)
  delete_pmachine ('pending remove')

Vmachine
  create_vmachine
  delete_vmachine
  start_vmachine
  stop_vmachine
  suspend_vmachine
  hibernate_vmachine (send data back to storage center) [experimental]
  resume_vmachine

Vcluster
  create_vcluster
  delete_vcluster
  start_vcluster
  stop_vcluster
  suspend_vcluster
  hibernate_vcluster
  resume_vcluster
  add_vmachine
  remove_vmachine

